===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ἀμέθυστος||not drunk|tr=amethustos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|ἀ-||not|tr=a-|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|μεθύω||I am drunk|tr=methuō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|μέθυ||wine|tr=methu|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}. The Greeks believed that the amethyst prevented [[intoxication]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[transparent]] [[purple]] variety of [[quartz]], used as a [[gemstone]].
# {{uncountable}} A [[purple]] [[colour]].
#: {{colour panel|amethyst|86608E}}
# {{heraldry}} The purple [[tincture]] when [[emblazon]]ing the [[arms]] of the English [[nobility]].

